'''Arfa Software Technology Park''' (previously known as '''Software Technology Park''') is an [[information technology]] park in [[Lahore]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]], built in 2009. It is home to the [[Information Technology University (Lahore)|Information Technology University]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.techlahore.com/2010/08/20/lahore-technology-park-software-park-almost-completed/ |title=Lahore Technology Park (Software Park) almost completed |publisher=TechLahore |date=20 August 2010 |accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://propakistani.pk/2009/07/09/another-software-it-park-in-lahore-converts-shaheen-complex/ |title=Another Software IT Park in Lahore, Converts Shaheen Complex |publisher=Propakistani.pk |date=9 July 2009 |accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://stp.pitb.gov.pk/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012024358/http://stp.pitb.gov.pk/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=12 October 2007 |title=Welcome to Software Technology Park, Lahore |publisher=Stp.pitb.gov.pk |date=3 July 2006 |accessdate=4 February 2012 }}</ref> and [[Punjab Information Technology Board|PITB]]. The main building consist of 17 floors and is 106 meters tall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pakiholic.com/top-20-tallest-buildings-in-pakistan/|title=Top 20 Tallest Buildings in Pakistan|last=|first=|date=|website=pakiholic.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-13}}</ref>
On 15 January 2012, Chief Minister of [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] Mian [[Shahbaz Sharif]] announced a name change of Software Technology Park to Arfa Software Technology Park after World's youngest [[Microsoft Certified Professional]] [[Arfa Karim]], who died at the age of 16.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2012/01/rip-arfa/|title=Arfa's death funeral|publisher=[[Pakistan Today]]|date=15 January 2012|accessdate=16 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=technologypark>{{cite news|url=http://www.thenews.com.pk/TodaysPrintDetail.aspx?ID=87791&Cat=2 |title=Software Technology Park name changed to Arfa Karim Technology Park |publisher=[[The News (Pakistan)|The News]] (newspaper) |date=16 January 2012 |accessdate=16 January 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120116101251/http://thenews.com.pk/TodaysPrintDetail.aspx?ID=87791&Cat=2 |archivedate=16 January 2012 }}</ref>
