{{Infobox NRHP | name = WestLoop&ndash;LaSalle Street Historic District | nrhp_type = hd | image = LaSalle Street from old Chicago Board of Trade Building.jpg | caption = LaSalle Street from the [[Chicago Board of Trade Building]], 1916 | location = Roughly bounded by W. Wacker Drive N. & S. Wells Street, W. Van Buren Street and N. & S. Clark Street; 330 S. Wells & 212 W. Van Buren Sts., [[Chicago, Illinois]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|52|50|N|87|37|56|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Chicago#Illinois#USA | added = June 1, 2013 | area = {{convert|70|acre}} | refnum = 12001238<ref name="NPS">{{cite web|title=Weekly List of Actions Taken on Properties: 6/03/13 Through 6/07/13|url=https://www.nps.gov/nr/listings/20130614.htm|publisher=[[National Park Service]]|accessdate=January 27, 2018|date=June 14, 2013}}</ref> }} The '''West Loop&ndash;LaSalle Street Historic District''' is a historic district centered on [[LaSalle Street]] in the western [[Chicago Loop]]. The district encompasses Chicago's financial center, which is anchored by the [[Chicago Board of Trade Building]], and also includes several of its major government buildings. Development in the district began in 1873 and, with the exception of a lull during the [[Great Depression]] and [[World War II]], has continued through the present day. Most of the district's buildings are [[high-rise building|high-rises]] with at least ten stories, with the tallest being the 49-story [[One North LaSalle Building]]. Many of Chicago's prominent architectural firms designed buildings within the district, and the buildings feature styles such as [[Classical Revival architecture|Classical Revival]], [[Chicago School (architecture)|Chicago School]], [[Art Deco]], [[Romanesque Revival architecture|Romanesque Revival]], and [[International Style (architecture)|International]]. Significant buildings within the district include the [[Federal Reserve Bank of Chicago]], [[Chicago City Hall]], and several office buildings for large banks and insurance companies.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Euer|first1=Danielle|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration Form: West Loop - LaSalle Street Historic District|url=http://gis.hpa.state.il.us/pdfs/801903.pdf|publisher=Illinois Historic Preservation Agency|accessdate=February 11, 2018|date=March 8, 2013}}</ref>
The district was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on June 1, 2013.<ref name="NPS"/> A boundary increase on July 24, 2017 added two buildings at 330 S. Wells Street and 212 W. Van Buren Street to the district.<ref>{{cite web|title=Weekly List of Actions Taken on Properties: 7/14/2017 Through 7/27/2017|url=https://www.nps.gov/nr/listings/20170728.htm|publisher=[[National Park Service]]|accessdate=January 27, 2018|date=July 28, 2017}}</ref>
